10:1 HIGH IMPEDANCE OSCILLOSCOPE PROBE NEEDS LOSSY CABLE
Probe-a(selfmade): probe with 50 Ohm cable, l=2m, R'=0 (lossless, standard coax)
Probe-b(selfmade): probe with 50 Ohm cable, l=2m, R'=100 Ohm/m, special cable
Probe-c(HP/Ag, Tek): their probes have typ. 100 Ohm cable, l=2m, R'=190 Ohm/m, special cable
R' is the ohmic resistance per 1m length of the inner conductor.
.AC analysis can be used also to see the "flat" frequency response.
Inner conductor with ohmic resistance of 100 Ohm/m
Inner conductor with ohmic resistance of 190 Ohm/m
We learn how useless a standard coaxial cable is for this purpose.
Probe cables need adapted high ohmic resistance of inner conductor.
Delay: Tpd/m = sqrt(L*C) = 5ns/m or v=1/sqrt(L*C) = 2/3*c0 choosen
Typical values are 100 Ohm/m to 200 Ohm/m depending on the cable's Z-impedance.
Z from dimensions: Z = 60/sqrt(Er)*log(D/d) [Ohm] , D/d = outer/inner diameter
